	<problem>
		<para>A house in <latex>\RNr[3]</latex> has the following corner points:</para>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<para>
					<latex>(0,0,0), (20,0,0), (0,16,0), (20,16,0)</latex>
				</para>
			</li>
			<li>
				<para>
					<latex>(0,0,10), (20,0,10), (0,16,10), (20,16,10)</latex>
				</para>
			</li>
			<li>
				<para>
					<latex>(0,8,20), (20,8,20)</latex>
				</para>
			</li>
		</ul>
		<para>Plot the points and sketch the house.</para>
	</problem>
	<approach>
		<answer>
			<para align="center"><img src="ims/HouseR3.gif" width="425" height="339"/></para>
		</answer>
		<solution.hint>
			<para>The base of the house lies in the <latex>xy</latex>-plane.</para>
		</solution.hint>
		<solution.hint>
			<para>The sides of the house are parallel to the coordinate planes.</para>
		</solution.hint>
	</approach>
</exercise>